com.jackmaney.factorization

Class Factorization<T extends Multiplicative<T> & java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jackmaney.factorization.Factorization<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - A type of object that implements Multiplicative and Comparable

    public class Factorization<T extends Multiplicative<T> & java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Given an object o of type T, this class represents a factorization of o into a product of Power objects (each having a distinct base).
    Author:
    Jack Maney

    • Constructor Detail

      • Factorization

        public Factorization(java.util.Vector<Power<T>> f)

        This constructor reshapes the argument to consolidate powers of any Power objects that have the same base.

        As a simple example using integers, if 3^4 (ie 3 to the fourth power) and 3^3 were each power elements, then they'd be combined into 3^7 in our factorization.

        Parameters:
        f - A Vector of Power objects, conceptually representing the factorization.

      • Factorization

        public Factorization(T[] arr)
        A similar constructor for an array of T values. In this case, the exponents for the Power objects are all considered to be 1.
        Parameters:
        arr -
